Russia RTS Stock-Index Futures Decline at Start of Trading

-- B y   H a l i a   P a v l i v a
-- 
2011-03-18T16:24:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-18/russia-rts-stock-index-futures-decline-at-start-of-trading.html
Russian RTS stock-index futures
expiring in June fell at the start of trading, declining 0.1
percent to 188,760 at 12:13 p.m. in  New York .  Contracts on OAO Sberbank,  Russia ’s largest lender, lost
0.2 percent and futures on OAO Gazprom, the natural-gas export
monopoly, declined 0.1 percent. Contracts on OAO Lukoil, the
country’s second-biggest oil producer, retreated 0.2 percent.
The Market Vectors Russia ETF, a U.S.-traded fund that holds
Russian shares, gained 0.3 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Halia Pavliva in New York at 
 hpavliva@bloomberg.net   To contact the editors responsible for this story:
